pageContext.claim: “[Car manufacturing plants] closed in Michigan, they closed in Ohio, they closed in other places.  Now they’re starting to move back.  Because of what we’ve done with regulation and with taxes, they’re starting to come back into our country in a big way.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump keeps taking credit for business decisions that predated him. It's simply wrong that companies are moving back to the United States for the "first time in many, many decades."
